{# ── What Changed Since 2018 ── #}
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <h2>What changed since 2018?</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--slate);margin-top:var(--space-sm);margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">Pflugerville voted on ACC annexation in 2018 and it failed 53.45% to 46.55%. Here is what is different now.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3>ACC launched free tuition</h3>
        <p>The free tuition pilot (2024) covers tuition for recent high school grads, but PfISD students still pay $201/credit hour in out-of-district fees. A Round Rock student pays $0. That gap did not exist in 2018.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3>Lockhart voted yes</h3>
        <p>Lockhart ISD joined the ACC district in November 2024 (61.2% yes). Enrollment tripled in one year. ACC opened a physical center with trade labs. Pflugerville now has a recent, comparable success story.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3>Workforce demand is growing</h3>
        <p>ACC workforce and healthcare enrollment grew double digits in 2025-26. Texas HB 8 (2023) shifted state funding to reward workforce credentials. PfISD is building a CTE center opening in 2027.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3>12 years, no tuition increase</h3>
        <p>ACC has not raised in-district tuition or general fees in 12 consecutive years. The tax rate ($0.1034/$100) is, per ACC, the lowest among Texas community colleges. The cost case is stronger than in 2018.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center mt-lg">
      <a href="/why-this-matters/" class="btn btn-secondary">Read the full story</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

